#: ../../M/memory-leak.rst:5
msgid "memory leak"
msgstr "memory leak"

#: ../../M/memory-leak.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../M/memory-leak.rst:9
msgid ""
"An error in a program's dynamic-store allocation logic that causes it to "
"fail to reclaim discarded memory, leading to eventual collapse due to memory"
" exhaustion. Also (esp. at CMU) called :ref:`core-leak`\\. These problems "
"were severe on older machines with small, fixed-size address spaces, and "
"special \"leak detection\" tools were commonly written to root them out. "
"With the advent of virtual memory, it is unfortunately easier to be sloppy "
"about wasting a bit of memory (although when you run out of memory on a VM "
"machine, it means you've got a *real* leak!). See :ref:`aliasing-bug`\\, "
":ref:`fandango-on-core`\\, :ref:`smash-the-stack`\\, :ref:`precedence-"
"lossage`\\, :ref:`overrun-screw`\\, :ref:`leaky-heap`\\, :ref:`leak`\\."
msgstr ""
"プログラムの動的記憶域割り当てロジックのエラーで、破棄されたメモリの回収に失敗し、メモリ枯渇による最終的な崩壊につながるもの。(特にCMUでは)\\ "
":ref:`core-leak`\\ "
"とも呼ばれる。これらの問題は、小さく固定サイズのアドレス空間を持つ古い機械では深刻で、それらを根絶するための特別な「リーク検出」ツールがよく書かれた。仮想メモリの登場により、残念ながら少しのメモリを浪費することにずさんになりやすくなった(ただしVMの機械でメモリを使い果たすときは、それは\\"
" *本物の*\\ リークがあるということだ!)。\\ :ref:`aliasing-bug`\\ 、\\ :ref:`fandango-on-"
"core`\\ 、\\ :ref:`smash-the-stack`\\ 、\\ :ref:`precedence-lossage`\\ 、\\ "
":ref:`overrun-screw`\\ 、\\ :ref:`leaky-heap`\\ 、\\ :ref:`leak`\\ を参照。"
